Google Analytics cookies 

Purpose: These are cookies provided by Google Inc. to monitor, in an anonymous and aggregate form, the statistical analysis of User traffic on the Platform to adapt the Platform to the results emerging from this analysis, in accordance with the interests shown by the Users themselves.
Collected data: data relating to the computer and the User's visit to the Platform and which, in no case, allow WeSchool to independently trace the Users' Personal Data: (i) the domain from which the Internet is accessed; (ii) the web address from which the User connected to the Platform, if available; (iii) the date and time of the connection with the Platform, how long it lasted and which pages were visited; (iv) the Internet protocol address (IP) of the User; (v) the computer operating system and the browser used by the User; (vi) the aggregate demographic detail of the Users who access the Platform.
Duration: Session cookies.

For more information on Google analytics, the User can consult the following web page: https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout.



 

WeSchool profiling cookies:

Purpose: WeSchool uses profiling cookies with the aim of improving the commercial experience of Users, by offering content modeled on personal tastes and habits, as well as sending advertising communications relating only to products that are most relevant to the interests of the User.
Data collected: data relating to the computer and the User's visit to the Platform, for the creation of a "navigation profile" of the User, based on the searches carried out by the latter and on the most consulted sections of the Platform.
Duration: session and permanent cookies.

Third party advertising cookies:

Purpose: Third-party advertising cookies are cookies provided by other websites to which WeSchool, through links or banners present within the Platform, refers, as they are third-party sites that have been found to be similar to the User's interests, to the for the purpose of sending information and commercial offers based on interests associated with the User's online activities. These Cookies do not personally identify Users.
Collected data: data and information on the User's guidelines and / or online preferences such as, for example, the searches carried out, the frequency of page loading or activity on other third party sites.
Duration: Session and permanent cookies.

For more information on third-party advertising cookies, the User can consult the following web page: https://www.manzoniadvertising.com/it/pages/Cookie_Concessionaria




13.     Acceptance and waiver of cookies
Consent, banners, access to browser control panels, Your Online Choices service


The User may give his consent to the use of the Cookies described in section 12 above using the methods indicated on the banner published on the Platform
The manifestation of consent can be modified at any time by the User according to the indications contained in this Information, which is accessible via the link in the banner and on each page of the Platform (footer). To this end, the User can also contact WeSchool at any time to obtain information about the concrete ways in which he can exercise his consent / selective refusal or delete cookies.
However, WeSchool specifies that disabling the technical cookies indicated in the previous section 12 could prevent correct navigation on the Platform and / or limit its usability. Consequently, in order to better use the WeSchool Services accessible through the Platform, the User is strongly discouraged from proceeding with the deactivation of these technical cookies.
Having said this, with reference to all the Cookies of the Platform, the User can change the settings relating to them, in the manner provided for in the control panels of the browser used, such as by way of example:

Google-Chrome: https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?hl=it-IT&hlrm=fr&hlrm=en
Mozilla-Firefox: https://support.mozilla.org/it/kb/Attivare%20e%20disattivare%20i%20cookie
Internet Explorer: https://support.microsoft.com/it-it/help/278835/how-to-delete-cookie-files-in-internet-explorer
Microsoft Edge: https://support.microsoft.com/it-it/help/4027947/microsoft-edge-delete-cookies
Safari: https://support.apple.com/it-it/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac

